@startuml oidc-flow
' DTA Brand: #0096FF (primary), #1A1A1A (text), #AAAAAA (muted), #FFFFFF (bg)

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 1.5
skinparam roundcorner 8
skinparam defaultFontColor #1A1A1A
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #0096FF
skinparam sequenceParticipantBackgroundColor #E8F4FF
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #AAAAAA
skinparam sequenceGroupBackgroundColor #F5F5F7
skinparam sequenceGroupBorderColor #0096FF
skinparam noteBorderColor #0096FF
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #E8F4FF
skinparam sequenceDividerBackgroundColor #E8F4FF
skinparam sequenceDividerBorderColor #0096FF
skinparam sequenceArrowColor #1A1A1A
skinparam sequenceMessageAlignment center

title <color:#0096FF>OIDC Authentication Flow with PKCE S256</color>

actor "User" as user #E8F4FF
participant "Browser" as browser #F5F5F7
participant "Vapor App\n(VaporSecurityKit)" as app #E8F4FF
participant "OIDC Provider\n(Auth0 / Entra)" as idp #CCE9FF
database "Session\nStore" as session #F5F5F7

== Login Flow (PKCE S256) ==

user -> browser: Click "Sign In"
browser -> app: GET /auth/login

app -> app: Generate code_verifier\n(cryptographic random)
app -> app: code_challenge =\nSHA256(code_verifier)
app -> session: Store code_verifier\n+ state nonce

app -> browser: 302 Redirect to IdP
browser -> idp: GET /authorize?\n  response_type=code&\n  code_challenge=<hash>&\n  code_challenge_method=S256&\n  state=<nonce>

note right of idp
  User authenticates
  (password, MFA, SSO)
end note

idp -> browser: 302 Redirect with\n  ?code=<auth_code>&state=<nonce>
browser -> app: GET /auth/callback?\n  code=<auth_code>&state=<nonce>

== Token Exchange ==

app -> session: Retrieve code_verifier\n+ validate state nonce
app -> idp: POST /oauth/token\n  code=<auth_code>&\n  code_verifier=<verifier>

note left of app
  PKCE: IdP verifies
  SHA256(verifier) matches
  the original challenge.
  No client secret needed
  for public clients.
end note

idp -> app: { access_token, id_token }

app -> app: Validate JWT signature\nvia JWKS endpoint
app -> app: Map claims to Principal\n(roles, tenant, email)

== Session Creation ==

app -> app: Create SessionData\n(HMAC-SHA256 signed\nwith current key)
app -> session: Store session token\nin signed cookie

app -> browser: 302 Redirect to /dashboard\nSet-Cookie: vsk_session=<token>
browser -> user: Dashboard (authenticated)

== Subsequent Requests ==

user -> browser: Navigate
browser -> app: GET /dashboard\nCookie: vsk_session=<token>

app -> app: PrincipalResolution:\nvalidate HMAC signature\n(try current key,\nfallback to previous key)
app -> app: Constant-time\nHMAC verification\n(timing-safe)

note right of app
  Dual-key rotation:
  SESSION_SECRET (current)
  SESSION_SECRET_PREVIOUS (old)
  Old sessions stay valid
  during key rotation.
end note

app -> browser: 200 OK (authorised content)

@enduml
